    "description": {
      "value": "\r\n<p><b>Price</b> 20 gp; <b>Weight</b> 1/2 lb.</p>\r\n<p>This kit contains three pliable suction cups, a constrictor strap, a tiny razor, and several vials of <a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/bestiary/monster-listings/animals/snake\">snake</a> antivenom. When suffering a <a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/gamemastering/afflictions/poison\">poison</a> that was delivered by the bite attack of a <a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/bestiary/monster-listings/animals/snake\">snake</a> (or other ophidian creature, such as a <a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/bestiary/monster-listings/monstrous-humanoids/serpentfolk\">serpentfolk</a>), as a <a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/gamemastering/combat#TOC-Full-Round-Actions\">full-round action</a>, you can use this kit to gain a +4 <a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/basics-ability-scores/glossary#TOC-Circumstance-Bonus\">circumstance bonus</a> on the ongoing <a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/gamemastering/combat#TOC-Fortitude\">Fortitude</a> saving throws against that <a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/gamemastering/afflictions/poison\">poison</a>. A snakebite kit is <a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/gamemastering/conditions#TOC-Exhausted\">exhausted</a> after 10 uses.</p>\r\n\r\n"
    },
